<section xml:id="objects_vocabulary"
         xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Vocabulary</title>
  <p>
    <dl>
      <li>
        <title>member functions or methods:</title>
        <p>
          <idx>
            <h>member function</h>
          </idx>
          <idx>
            <h>method</h>
          </idx> A function that is part of a class. They are always called on a particular object of that class.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <title>encapsulation:</title>
        <p>
          <idx>
            <h>encapsulation</h>
          </idx> Tying data and functions that work on that data together into one package. </p>
      </li>

      <li>
        <title>UML:</title>
        <p>
          <idx>
            <h>UML</h>
          </idx> Unified Modeling Language, a standard way to draw diagrams
          for software engineering.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <title>class:</title>
        <p>
          <idx>
            <h>class</h>
          </idx> A user defined data type that encapsulates a collection of data with methods to work with that data.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <title>class diagram:</title>
        <p>
          <idx>
            <h>class diagram</h>
          </idx> An illustration of the attributes and functions for
          a class.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <title>information hiding:</title>
        <p>
          <idx>
            <h>information hiding</h>
          </idx> Limiting access to pieces of data to particular parts of the code. Classes generally use information hiding to prevent other code from directly accessing member variables.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <title>mutable:</title>
        <p>
          <idx>
            <h>mutable</h>
          </idx> An object that can be modified at any time. Points and
          rectangles are mutable by design.</p>
      </li>
    </dl>
  </p>
</section>